HEADWORD: Pentamerus
<hw>Pen*tam"e*rus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Pentamerous</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A genus of
extinct Paleozoic brachiopods, often very abundant in the Upper
Silurian.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pentamerus limestone</b></col> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>, <cd>a
Silurian limestone composed largely of the shells of
Pentamerus.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pentameter</ent>⟦br⟧
